OL,3,CGovernment urged not to weaken
OL,4,C'Hillsborough Law'
OL,6,FMeanwhile his party colleague
OL,7,FLiverpool and West Derby MP Ian Byrne
OL,8,Fasked for the Bill to be "worthy of
OL,9,Fthe name".
OL,11,FThe proposed law would require public
OL,12,Fbodies to have a duty of candour,
OL,13,Fmeaning they would need to co-operate
OL,14,Fwith official inquiries and tell the
OL,15,Ftruth in the aftermath of major
OL,16,Fdisasters ` or face criminal sanctions.
OL,18,FA previous deadline set by Labour,
OL,19,Fthat the Bill would be passed before
OL,20,Fthe anniversary of the Hillsborough
OL,21,Fdisaster in April, has been missed.
OL,26,@pD@ZOUqD@IO]
